-- Russia Posts 6-Month Budget Surplus of 247.4 Billion Rubles
-- B y   A l e x   N i c h o l s o n
-- 2012-07-12T10:25:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-12/russia-posts-6-month-budget-surplus-of-247-4-billion-rubles-1-.html
Russia’s  federal budget  had a
surplus of 247.4 billion rubles ($7.56 billion) in the first six
months of the year, equivalent to 0.9 percent of gross domestic
product, the Finance Ministry said on its website today.  Revenue in the period was 6.199 trillion rubles, and
spending was 5.952 trillion rubles, the ministry’s data show.  To contact the reporter on this story:
